    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="7"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d7">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 Chiang Kai-shek/1–549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-05">January 5,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received January 4—11:29 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. North Shensi radio Chinese voicecast last night featured very strongly worded
                    New China News Agency editorial which rejected New Year’s Day “peace plot” by
                    “China’s No. 1 war criminal Chiang Kai-shek”, on grounds that the Kmt
                    reactionaries and “American imperialists” are only maneuvering to obtain respite
                    for purpose of reconstructing their armed forces for further “imperialist
                    aggression” against CCP. This news has not yet been broadcast.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 26, repeated Shanghai 16.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
